  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C / 425&deg;F/ Gas 7&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice into rounds</p>\r\n<p>Trim, then slice the&nbsp;<strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>leek</strong> and<strong> courgette</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;then put the tray in the oven for an initial 10-15 min or until step 3</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>wheat berries</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> (the same as you would for pasta)</p>\r\n<p>Cook over a high heat for 10-12 min</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and set aside</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces</p>\r\n<p>Remove the tray of <strong>vegetables</strong> from the oven and add the <strong>chicken</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and return the tray to the oven for 15 min or until everything's cooked&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, re-boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong>&nbsp;parsley</strong>&nbsp;finely, including the stalks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;chopped parsley</strong>&nbsp;to a<strong> pestle &amp; mortar</strong> with the&nbsp;<strong>capers</strong>, 2 tbsp&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]&nbsp;</span><strong>warm water</strong>&nbsp;and a generous pinch of<strong>&nbsp;salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grind to a paste, then add 1 tbsp&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]&nbsp;</span><strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;and mix to combine &ndash; this is your&nbsp;<strong>salsa verde&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1322.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the&nbsp;<strong>green beans&nbsp;</strong>in half&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the&nbsp;<strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the<strong> chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>in 500ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
